{"questionId":"3379039","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the cost of materials, to the nearest dollar, to construct all <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>350</mn></math> containers.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to calculate the cost of one container&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>34621</mn><mo>…</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>7</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> May be shown within a calculation of the cost of all containers.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6895</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6895</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mn>350</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>$</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8641</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Answer must be rounded to the nearest dollar to award the final<em><strong> A1</strong></em>. <br><br>Accept answers between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8641</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8645</mn></math> (inclusive), due to rounding the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and/or the cost of one container to the nearest cent.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> for an answer rounded to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>sf (e.g. (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo></math>)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8640</mn></math>) or to 2dp (e.g., (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo></math>)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8641</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>35</mn></math>).</p>\n<p>Accept an answer of (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo></math>)<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8638</mn></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>$</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>34</mn></math> in their cost calculation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3379039","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.5e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the cost of materials, to the nearest dollar, to construct all 350 containers.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Approximating and estimating"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}